(2) Any other person from disclosing facts related to sexual abuse against a minor in
support of, in furtherance of, or consistent with the right of a victim or alleged victim
to disclose under proposed law.
Proposed law provides that notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, nothing in
proposed law shall be construed to prohibit a person, including a victim or alleged victim
of sexual abuse against a minor, from entering into a contract or agreement that restricts the
disclosure of information, including the amount or payment terms of a settlement, by another
party to the contract or agreement, including an alleged perpetrator, provided that such
restriction does not prevent disclosure protected pursuant to proposed law.
Proposed law provides that no person may enforce or attempt to enforce a nondisclosure
clause provided for in proposed law, regardless of the date that the contract or agreement
containing the nondisclosure clause was entered into.
Proposed law provides that the provisions of proposed law shall apply retroactively and
prospectively to any nondisclosure clause in a contract or agreement entered into before, on,
or after the date of proposed law.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
